          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Eval Integration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Eval integration is the practice of turning user feedback into structured, versioned evaluation cases that run as automated quality gates in CI. Rather than maintaining a static benchmark that quickly becomes stale, a feedback-driven eval set grows continuously from production failures, preserving the exact prompts and contexts where the model let users down. This makes the eval suite a living record of known hard cases, and makes CI a meaningful guard against shipping regressions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Eval integration pipeline: production feedback \u2192 eval store \u2192 eval runner \u2192 CI gate \u2192 deploy or block"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Eval Store Schema"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each eval case stores the input prompt, an optional golden response, a machine-readable rubric, the source feedback ID, and a version tag. A separate "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "eval_results",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " table records every run's score for comparison over time:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "sql"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "-- Versioned eval case store\nCREATE TABLE eval_cases (\n    id                  UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n    input_prompt        TEXT NOT NULL,\n    golden_response     TEXT,            -- human-authored ideal answer (may be NULL for rubric-only cases)\n    rubric              JSONB,           -- evaluation criteria as structured JSON\n    category            TEXT NOT NULL,   -- 'regression' | 'safety' | 'factual' | 'style' | 'task_specific'\n    source_feedback_id  UUID REFERENCES llm_feedback(id),\n    split               TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'dev',  -- 'dev' | 'test'\n    version_tag         TEXT NOT NULL,   -- e.g. 'v2024-06-15'\n    added_by            TEXT,\n    created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE eval_results (\n    id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n    case_id       UUID REFERENCES eval_cases(id),\n    model_id      TEXT NOT NULL,\n    run_id        TEXT NOT NULL,         -- one run = one CI job\n    score         NUMERIC(4,3),          -- 0.000\u20131.000\n    pass          BOOLEAN NOT NULL,\n    response_text TEXT,\n    judge_rationale TEXT,\n    ran_at        TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "source_feedback_id",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " foreign key is critical: it lets you trace every eval case back to the original production failure, and lets you audit whether the golden response or rubric was correct when reviewing a case that keeps failing on new models."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Feedback \u2192 Eval Case Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Converting Reviewed Feedback into Cases"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Not every negative feedback event becomes an eval case. The workflow is: auto-tag \u2192 sample for human review \u2192 human annotates rubric + ideal response \u2192 persist as eval case. The conversion function encapsulates this:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\nimport uuid\n\n@dataclass\nclass EvalCase:\n    input_prompt: str\n    golden_response: Optional[str]\n    rubric: dict\n    category: str\n    source_feedback_id: str\n    split: str = \"dev\"\n\ndef feedback_to_eval_case(feedback_record: dict, human_annotation: dict) -> EvalCase:\n    \"\"\"Convert a reviewed feedback event into a versioned eval case.\"\"\"\n    prompt, response = get_turn_text(feedback_record[\"response_id\"])\n    category = human_annotation.get(\"category\", feedback_record.get(\"label\", \"other\"))\n\n    # Build rubric from human annotation\n    rubric = {\n        \"criteria\": human_annotation.get(\"criteria\", [\n            \"Response is factually accurate\",\n            \"Response directly addresses the user's question\",\n            \"Response is appropriately concise\",\n        ]),\n        \"threshold\": human_annotation.get(\"threshold\", 0.8),\n        \"failure_reason\": human_annotation.get(\"failure_reason\", \"\"),\n    }\n\n    return EvalCase(\n        input_prompt=prompt,\n        golden_response=human_annotation.get(\"ideal_response\"),\n        rubric=rubric,\n        category=category,\n        source_feedback_id=feedback_record[\"id\"],\n        split=\"test\" if category == \"safety\" else \"dev\",\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Human reviewers provide three things: the corrected "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ideal_response",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (if they know it), a set of plain-English "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "criteria",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " the response should satisfy, and the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "failure_reason",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " from the original interaction. Cases without a golden response use rubric-only evaluation by LLM-as-judge."
          }
        ]
